For me surfing has been like breathing, I never thought about it I just did it. It was a part of me. After birthing two babies and not surfing for 10 months surfing is now HUMBLING and a mixture of so many emotions… hard,upsetting,embarrassing and peaceful. My mind knows what it wants to do on a wave but my body just can’t! I can barely paddle back out without every muscle feeling so incredibly weak. Being in the water gives me so much clarity and helps me be the best me. I guess I took it for granted and didn’t realize how much surfing and salt water heals your mind when it comes to day to day life stressors. And how much I need it! My new normal isn’t what I thought it was going to be. I thought my boys would come into this world and I’d just be back to hanging 10 but nope, I’m trying to navigate this new body. I used to be filled with so much pride when I would come in from surfing a really good wave and be proud of myself. Today, I was filled with an overwhelming amount of pride and love when I came in from surfing because my two little boys were watching me with bright eyes eager to explore the world. #postpartumisatrip #newmom #twins
Best year of our lives!! Our hearts quadrupled in size!!! Can’t wait for what’s in store for 2024🥰
